**Recipe**

(1)
Bok Choy with Rice
	Bok Choy with rice is a traditional soul food in Hong Kong and also easy to prepared. First preheat the pan, adding oil and diced sausages. Slice garlics and fried with the meat until going brown and smells good. Next, add some minced ginger and chopped Bok Choy. Cook until water comes out from the vegetable and you can add a little bit salt for seasoning. After that, add the washed raw rice into the pan and stir-fried until it’s average. Pour the chicken soup into the pan until the soup covers the other materials. Close the lid and steam with small fire about twenty minutes. Finally, close the fire and wait five minutes. The rice will be well cooked. Now this meal is not only smells good but looks great.

